# pi-gen-nclawzero / authorized_keys.example
#
# THIS FILE IS COMMITTED.  Documents the format expected by the
# stage-zeroclaw/04-bake-authorized-keys stage. The actual fleet-internal
# key list lives at the sibling path `authorized_keys` (no .example
# suffix), which is gitignored — never published to gitlab.com / github.com.
#
# To populate before building:
#
#   1. cp stage-zeroclaw/04-bake-authorized-keys/files/authorized_keys.example \
#         stage-zeroclaw/04-bake-authorized-keys/files/authorized_keys
#
#   2. Replace the placeholder lines below with your fleet's real
#      ssh-ed25519 / ssh-rsa pubkey lines.
#
#   3. Sanity-check: `git status` must NOT show
#      stage-zeroclaw/04-bake-authorized-keys/files/authorized_keys as
#      tracked — the .gitignore rule keeps it local-only.
#
# Format (one key per line, comment field is informational):
#   ssh-<type> <base64> <comment-descriptive-of-workstation>
#
# Idempotency: every rebuild replaces /home/<user>/.ssh/authorized_keys
# wholesale on the produced image; nothing accumulates across re-builds.
# Rotation = edit this file + rebuild image + reflash.
#
# Both targets (FIRST_USER_NAME — typically ncz — and the jasonperlow
# backup user) get the SAME authorized_keys content. The second user
# is a defense-in-depth foothold for when the operator account is
# disrupted (cf. 2026-04-26 Trixie userconfig stripping clawpi+zeropi
# accounts at first boot).

# Replace these placeholder lines with real fleet workstation keys:
ssh-ed25519 AAAAREPLACEME jperlow@<workstation-name>
# ssh-ed25519 AAAAREPLACEME <user>@<host>
